{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id1286f725-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"§ 6.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Time and occasions for display","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id1286f726-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s6/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" It is the universal custom to display the flag only from sunrise to sunset on buildings and on stationary flagstaffs in the open. However, when a patriotic effect is desired, the flag may be displayed 24 hours a day if properly illuminated during the hours of darkness.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id1286f727-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s6/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The flag should be hoisted briskly and lowered ceremoniously.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id1286f728-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s6/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The flag should not be displayed on days when the weather is inclement, except when an all weather flag is displayed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id1286f729-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s6/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The flag should be displayed on all days, especially on New Year’s Day, January 1; Inauguration Day, January 20; Martin Luther King Jr.’s birthday, third Monday in January; Lincoln’s Birthday, February 12; Washington’s Birthday, third Monday in February; National Vietnam War Veterans Day, March 29; Easter Sunday (variable); Mother’s Day, second Sunday in May; Armed Forces Day, third Saturday in May; Memorial Day (half-staff until noon), the last Monday in May; Flag Day, June 14; Father’s Day, third Sunday in June; Independence Day, July 4; National Korean War Veterans Armistice Day, July 27; Labor Day, first Monday in September; Constitution Day, September 17; Columbus Day, second Monday in October; Navy Day, October 27; Veterans Day, November 11; Thanksgiving Day, fourth Thursday in November; Christmas Day, December 25; and such other days as may be proclaimed by the President of the United States; the birthdays of States (date of admission); and on State holidays.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id1286f72a-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s6/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The flag should be displayed daily on or near the main administration building of every public institution.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id1286f72b-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s6/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The flag should be displayed in or near every polling place on election days.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id1286f72c-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c","identifier":"/us/usc/t4/s6/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The flag should be displayed during school days in or near every schoolhouse.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id1286f72d-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/225/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–225, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-08-12"},"text":"Aug. 12, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/1494"},"text":"112 Stat. 1494","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/80/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–80, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-10-25"},"text":"Oct. 25, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1285"},"text":"113 Stat. 1285","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/239/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–239, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-06-03"},"text":"June 3, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/1559"},"text":"122 Stat. 1559","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/41/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–41, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-07-27"},"text":"July 27, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/1962"},"text":"123 Stat. 1962","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/15/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–15, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-03-28"},"text":"Mar. 28, 2017","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/131/79"},"text":"131 Stat. 79","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id1286f72e-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id1286f72f-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"id1286f730-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c"},"text":"